cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless link and QoS, which are related to networking. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the effect of path loss on link quality, which is a topic related to information theory. 
- cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is another possible category as the paper deals with wireless communication and spectrum allocation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses a method to dynamically allocate spectrum for link improvement, which can be seen as a control system. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also a less likely category, but the paper mentions the use of software defined radio (SDR) in the RF front end, which can be related to hardware architecture.
